==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Eighty
<hw>Eight"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[AS.
<ets>eahtatig</ets>, where the ending <ets>-tig</ets> is akin to English
<ets>ten</ets>; cf. G. <ets>achtzig</ets>. See <er>Eight</er>, and
<er>Ten</er>.]</ety> <def>Eight times ten; fourscore.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eighty</ent>⟦br⟧

==== ENTRY 2 ====
HEADWORD: Eighty
<hw>Eight"y</hw>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The sum of eight times
ten; eighty units or objects.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A symbol representing eighty units, or ten eight
times repeated, as 80 or lxxx.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Eigne</ent>⟦br⟧
